{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"39a65751-63c8-4a81-a680-faf909fc06d3","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages with version `10.x` (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) and bump those to their `11.x` equivalents. Review the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/migration) for any breaking changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9b61c22d-728b-401e-9812-36c16294b893","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files. Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":323,"requestId":"8852:2E7316:1E52AA9:21D2CCB:69FA9D30"},"id":"a167fc57-061c-4eb7-b88f-abddacd5f75d","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:45:27.908Z","parentId":"004151e6-c080-4636-b894-2bfe9fbf8a49"}
